## 🎯 Overview

TaskFlow is a feature-rich task and project management system built with Laravel and MySQL. It provides teams with powerful tools to organize work, track progress, and collaborate effectively. With role-based access control, Google OAuth integration, interactive calendar views, and comprehensive reporting capabilities, TaskFlow adapts to your team's workflow.

## ✨ Key Features

### 🔐 Authentication & Security
- **Dual Authentication**: Manual login with email verification and Google OAuth via Laravel Socialite
- **Secure Sessions**: Password encryption and secure session management
- **Role-Based Middleware**: Dynamic permission sets based on user roles
- **Soft Delete Protection**: Deactivated users retain view-only access with alert notifications

### 👥 User Management
- Complete CRUD operations for user accounts
- Bulk deletion and advanced search functionality
- Role assignment and permission management
- Real-time activity tracking
- Team organization and hierarchy

### 📁 Project Management
- Create and manage unlimited projects
- Assign project managers and team members
- Filter projects by creator or assigned manager
- Project-level task organization
- Progress tracking and reporting

### ✅ Advanced Task Management
- **Smart Task Creation**: Set priority levels, status, and deadlines
- **Tag System**: Quick categorization with visual tags (bug, design, meeting, review, etc.)
- **Inline Editing**: Update status, priority, and assignee without page reload
- **Advanced Filtering**: Filter by project, user, priority, status, and date range
- **Discussion Threads**: Threaded comments and replies on each task
- **Real-time Updates**: Live task status changes across the system

### 🗓️ Interactive Calendar Dashboard
- **Multiple Views**: Day, week, and month calendar layouts
- **Visual Task Overview**: Color-coded status badges for each task
- **Interactive Navigation**: Click dates to view detailed task information
- **Deadline Tracking**: Never miss an important due date

### 📊 Comprehensive Reporting
- Generate custom reports based on multiple filters
- **Export Formats**: PDF, Excel, Word, and PowerPoint
- Role-based report access and visibility
- Data visualization and analytics

### 💡 Additional Features
- **Responsive Design**: Glassmorphism-inspired UI with Bootstrap 5.3.2
- **Font Awesome Icons**: Modern, intuitive iconography
- **Email Notifications**: Automated alerts for task assignments and updates
- **Activity Logs**: Track all system activities and changes

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer                  | Technology |
|------------------------|------------|
| **Backend Framework**  | Laravel 12 (PHP 8.1+) |
| **Database**           | MySQL |
| **Frontend** | Bootstrap 5.3.2 + Custom CSS (Glassmorphism) |
| **Icons** | Font Awesome 6 |
| **Authentication** | Laravel Socialite (Google OAuth) |
| **Export Libraries** | TCPDF, PhpSpreadsheet, PhpWord, PhpPresentation |

---

## 📦 Prerequisites

Before installing TaskFlow, ensure your system meets these requirements:

- **PHP** >= 8.1
- **Composer** (latest version)
- **MySQL** >= 5.7 or **MariaDB** >= 10.3
- **Node.js** and **NPM** (for asset compilation)
- **Git** (for cloning the repository)
- **Web Server** (Apache/Nginx) or use Laravel's built-in server

---

## 🚀 Installation

### Step 1: Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Dwip-Pandya/task-management-system.git
cd task-management-system
```

### Step 2: Install Dependencies

```bash
# Install PHP dependencies
composer install

# Install Node dependencies (if using npm)
npm install
```

### Step 3: Environment Setup

```bash
# Copy the example environment file
cp .env.example .env

# Generate application key
php artisan key:generate
```

---

## ⚙️ Configuration

### Database Configuration

Edit your `.env` file and configure the database settings:

```env
DB_CONNECTION=mysql
DB_HOST=127.0.0.1
DB_PORT=3306
DB_DATABASE=task_management_system
DB_USERNAME=your_database_username
DB_PASSWORD=your_database_password
```

### Google OAuth Configuration

To enable Google login, you need to set up OAuth credentials:

1. Go to [Google Cloud Console](https://console.cloud.google.com/)
2. Create a new project or select an existing one
3. Enable Google+ API
4. Create OAuth 2.0 credentials
5. Add authorized redirect URI: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/google/callback`
6. Add credentials to your `.env` file:

```env
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_client_secret
GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI=http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/google/callback
```

### Mail Configuration (Optional)

For email notifications and verification:

```env
MAIL_MAILER=smtp
MAIL_HOST=smtp.gmail.com
MAIL_PORT=587
MAIL_USERNAME=your_email@gmail.com
MAIL_PASSWORD=your_app_password
MAIL_ENCRYPTION=tls
MAIL_FROM_ADDRESS=your_email@gmail.com
MAIL_FROM_NAME="${APP_NAME}"
```

---

## 💾 Database Setup

### Run Migrations and Seeders

```bash
# Run all migrations
php artisan migrate

# Seed the database with initial data
php artisan db:seed

# Or run both together
php artisan migrate --seed
```

The seeder will create default users for each role with the following credentials:

| Role | Email | Password |
|------|-------|----------|
| Admin | admin@taskflow.com | password |
| Project Manager | manager@taskflow.com | password |
| Project Member | member@taskflow.com | password |
| User | user@taskflow.com | password |

> ⚠️ **Important**: Change these default passwords in production!

---

## 🎮 Usage

### Starting the Development Server

```bash
php artisan serve
```

Access the application at: **http://127.0.0.1:8000**

### Default Login

Use the seeded credentials above to log in and explore different role capabilities.

### Creating Your First Project

1. Log in as Admin or Project Manager
2. Navigate to "Projects" in the sidebar
3. Click "Create New Project"
4. Fill in project details and assign team members
5. Start creating tasks!

### Managing Tasks

1. Go to the "Tasks" section
2. Click "Create Task" and fill in details
3. Assign priority, status, and tags
4. Use inline editing to quickly update task properties
5. Add comments for team collaboration

### Using the Calendar

1. Navigate to the "Calendar" page
2. Switch between Day, Week, and Month views
3. Click on any date to see tasks due that day
4. Color-coded badges indicate task status at a glance

### Generating Reports

1. Go to "Reports" section
2. Select filters (date range, project, user, status, etc.)
3. Choose export format (PDF, Excel, Word, PowerPoint)
4. Click "Generate Report"

---

## 👤 Roles & Permissions

TaskFlow implements a comprehensive role-based access control system:

### 🔴 Admin
- **Full System Access**: Complete CRUD operations on all entities
- **User Management**: Create, edit, and soft delete users
- **Project Oversight**: Manage all projects across the organization
- **Task Control**: View and manage all tasks
- **Reporting**: Generate and export all reports
- **Calendar Access**: Full calendar view and management

### 🟡 Project Manager
- **Project Management**: Create and manage assigned projects
- **Task Assignment**: Create tasks and assign to team members
- **Team Coordination**: Manage project team members
- **Progress Tracking**: Monitor project and task progress
- **Reporting**: Generate project-specific reports
- **Calendar**: View project deadlines and milestones

### 🟢 Project Member
- **Task Updates**: View and update assigned tasks
- **Collaboration**: Comment on tasks and participate in discussions
- **Status Reporting**: Update task progress and status
- **Calendar View**: See personal task deadlines
- **Limited Reporting**: View reports for assigned projects

### 🔵 User
- **Personal Tasks**: Create and manage own tasks
- **Task Collaboration**: Comment on assigned tasks
- **Calendar**: View personal task schedule
- **Profile Management**: Update own profile information

### ⚠️ Soft-Deleted Users
- **View-Only Access**: Can log in but cannot perform CRUD operations
- **Alert Notification**: Header displays deactivation status
- **Data Preservation**: All historical data remains visible
- **Read-Only Mode**: Cannot create, edit, or delete any content

